The paper focuses on object detection using UAV images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of region-based CNNs is a popular approach for object detection (cs.RO), and the paper specifically modifies the faster R-CNN model. The paper also discusses the use of multi-class detection, which involves classification and could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The modifications made to the model, such as replacing the RoI pooling layer, could be considered a form of optimization and could fall under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the use of annotated labels and training a model, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
